# Line-ending normalization — this is a DETERMINISM control, not cosmetics.
#
# Notebook B-01 records the unexpected truth that VV-101 decision-log hashes came out
# bit-identical across Windows (local), macOS CI, and Windows CI. That property is the
# foundation of ADR-109 (replay determinism) and the VV-101 release gate.
#
# Git's default autocrlf behaviour rewrites line endings per-platform on checkout. Any
# byte-wise comparison of corpus inputs or evidence artifacts across a Windows dev box
# and a macOS runner would then silently diverge — determinism would die quietly, which
# is exactly the class of failure D20 warns about (a broken gate that still looks green).
#
# Therefore: LF everywhere, in the repo AND in every working tree, on every platform.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Everything the harness reads, hashes, or emits — pinned explicitly.
*.swift  text eol=lf
*.json   text eol=lf
*.yml    text eol=lf
*.yaml   text eol=lf
*.md     text eol=lf
*.sh     text eol=lf

# Never touch binaries.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
